HB 656 Reengrossed 2026 Regular Session Bryant
Abstract: Creates a pilot program that provides certain Dept. of Public Safety and
Corrections (DPS&C) programming and services to inmates.
Proposed law authorizes DPS&C, subject to the availability of funding and resources, to
establish the Access to Programming Pilot Program to be administered by inmates who are
qualified and approved by DPS&C for the purpose of making programming available to
certain offenders.
Proposed law provides for services to be included within the programming and options for
attendance.
Proposed law requires DPS&C to adopt rules and regulations in accordance with the APA
to implement the provisions of proposed law.
(Adds R.S. 15:830.4)
Summary of Amendments Adopted by House
The House Floor Amendments to the engrossed bill:
1. Provide that the Access to Programming Pilot Program is to be administered by
inmates who are qualified and approved by the department.
